  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-Employment preservation: through capacity increase and efficiency gains, the Project helps to maintain and further create employment at the Company -Continued know-how and technology transfers: given the Group&apos;&apos;s focus on product innovation and its ability to meet stringent quality standards, the Project is expected to result in continued technology and know-how transfer through the expansion of the Company&apos;&apos;s operations into PET.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed modernization Project entails the replacement of obsolete equipment with more efficient machinery at Nile Kordsa Company for Industrial Fabrics S.A.E (the Company). Based in 10th of  Ramadan City, Area No. 7, Industrial Zone B1 Egypt, the Company is a joint venture between Kordsa Global Endustriyel Iplik ve Kord Bezi Sanayi ve Ticaret A.S. (Kordsa or the Group) and the Egyptian Partners focusing on tire cord fabric processing. The Project will increase the Companys production capacity and enable it to expand its product offering.</narrative>
  </description>
